I want to add the chrom-devtools-mcp from github to my global claude code configuration (the directory we are currently in!). here's some relevant info: 
Add the following config to your MCP client:

{
  "mcpServers": {
    "chrome-devtools": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "chrome-devtools-mcp@latest"]
    }
  }
}

Use the Claude Code CLI to add the Chrome DevTools MCP server (guide):
claude mcp add chrome-devtools npx chrome-devtools-mcp@latest

the create an agent called ChromeMaster with proper configuuration (checkout the other agents), search the web for https://github.com/ChromeDevTools/chrome-devtools-mcp?tab=readme-ov-file#your-first-prompt to get the info, add to the agents instructions details for using chrome dev tools mcp. make sure the agent is configured to Haiku 4.5 .

